casebody.data:
Lewis Weldon v. Mildred M. Weldon

King, C. J., Alcorn, House, Thim and Ryan, Js.

Argued December 3 decided December 17, 1968 *600James N. Egan, for the appellant (plaintiff). Norris L. O’Neill, for the appellee (defendant). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed since the subordinate facts found support the referee’s conclusions and no error of law appears.

There is no error.
